              "explanation": "Labile affect describes rapid, unpredictable shifts in emotional expression. This pattern — quickly transitioning between euphoria, tearfulness, and anger — is characteristic of labile affect, commonly seen in mania, borderline personality disorder, and some neurological conditions. Constricted/blunted refer to reduced range; incongruent means affect does not match stated mood or thought content."
