              "explanation": "Alogia (poverty of thought/speech) is characterized by reduced quantity of speech with limited content — a negative symptom of schizophrenia or severe depression. Thought blocking = abrupt cessation mid-sentence. Mutism = complete absence of speech. Perseveration = repetitive return to the same idea."
