              "title": "The Late Night Call",
              "type": "case",
              "content": "**2:17 AM.** Your pager goes off. Nursing calls: \"Patient in Room 4 said to her roommate: 'I won't be here much longer.' Roommate is scared. Can you come assess?\"\n\nYou walk in. Luz, 34F, admitted for depression, is lying in bed facing the wall. She says without turning: \"I knew they'd send someone.\"\n\n**Key tension:** She's told you indirectly she's in distress, but she hasn't asked for help. How do you approach this? What do you ask first? What do you NOT say?\n\n*This lesson teaches you exactly how to navigate this moment.*"
