              "explanation": "Blockade of D2 receptors in the nigrostriatal pathway disrupts normal motor control, producing extrapyramidal symptoms (EPS): akathisia, acute dystonia, parkinsonism, and tardive dyskinesia. The mesolimbic pathway mediates antipsychotic efficacy. Mesocortical blockade worsens negative symptoms. Tuberoinfundibular blockade causes hyperprolactinemia."
