              "explanation": "Treatment-resistant schizophrenia is defined as failure of ≥2 adequate antipsychotic trials (different chemical classes, adequate dose, adequate duration). Clozapine is the only evidence-based treatment for treatment-resistant schizophrenia and is significantly underutilized. It requires regular CBC monitoring due to risk of agranulocytosis (1%). Polypharmacy, pushing doses above maximum, and LAIs don't address treatment resistance."
