              "explanation": "Aripiprazole (and brexpiprazole) are partial D2 agonists — they provide partial stimulation at D2 receptors rather than full blockade. In hyperdopaminergic states (mesolimbic), they reduce activity; in hypodopaminergic states (mesocortical), they maintain some activation. This partial agonism explains weight neutrality and the 'activating' side effect (agitation, insomnia, akathisia at higher doses). Full D2 antagonism characterizes haloperidol, olanzapine, and quetiapine."
