              "explanation": "Per ADA/APA guidelines, fasting glucose should be checked at baseline, at 12 weeks (when early metabolic changes emerge), then annually thereafter. Weight should be checked more frequently (monthly for 3 months then quarterly). Olanzapine and clozapine carry highest metabolic risk and warrant vigilant monitoring."
