              "explanation": "Risk factors for QTc-related arrhythmia include: electrolyte abnormalities (hypokalemia, hypomagnesemia), use of multiple QTc-prolonging drugs, female sex (women have inherently longer baseline QTc), pre-existing cardiac disease (structural or arrhythmic), and high baseline QTc. Correction of electrolytes is an important and modifiable intervention. Diet does not significantly affect QTc."
