              "explanation": "Metformin has the strongest evidence base for antipsychotic-induced weight gain, particularly for clozapine and olanzapine. Multiple RCTs show it reduces weight, fasting glucose, and insulin resistance. It also does not worsen psychiatric symptoms and is generally well-tolerated. While topiramate and bupropion have some evidence, metformin is considered first-line for antipsychotic-induced weight gain."
