              "explanation": "QTc 450-500 ms = borderline/monitoring range, not absolute contraindication. QTc &gt;500 ms = stop the drug and reassess. Check concurrent QT-prolonging medications (antibiotics, antiemetics). The decision is individualized based on psychiatric need, alternatives, and ongoing monitoring. Magnesium has no proven role in antipsychotic-induced QTc prolongation."
