              "explanation": "Quetiapine has 'fast off' kinetics at the D2 receptor — it binds and dissociates quickly. This loose D2 binding translates to antipsychotic efficacy with minimal EPS risk, as the nigrostriatal pathway is not continuously blocked. This is the same principle that makes clozapine low in EPS."
