              "explanation": "TCAs have equivalent antidepressant efficacy to SSRIs. However, their lethality in overdose (as few as 5–7 doses can be fatal), anticholinergic side effects (dry mouth, constipation, urinary retention, confusion in elderly), orthostatic hypotension, and cardiac toxicity led to SSRIs replacing them as first-line treatment. TCAs remain valuable for specific indications (neuropathic pain, OCD, TRD)."
