              "explanation": "This is classic anticholinergic toxicity: dry mouth (decreased salivation), blurry vision (pupil dilation/cycloplegia), urinary retention (detrusor muscle inhibition), and confusion/delirium (central anticholinergic syndrome). All TCAs (especially tertiary amines) block muscarinic receptors. Management: supportive care, physostigmine for severe central toxicity."
