            "MAOIs are the most effective antidepressant class for atypical depression (mood reactivity + reversed neurovegetative features: hypersomnia, hyperphagia, leaden paralysis, rejection sensitivity).",
            "Hypertensive crisis from tyramine: MAO-A normally breaks down dietary tyramine in gut/liver; if inhibited, tyramine enters systemic circulation → massive NE/catecholamine release → hypertensive crisis.",
            "The washout period before starting an MAOI after an SSRI is 14 days (5 weeks for fluoxetine due to long half-life of norfluoxetine).",
