              "explanation": "'Sickness behavior' is an evolutionarily conserved response to infection: fatigue, anhedonia, reduced appetite, social withdrawal, hypersomnia, and increased pain sensitivity. These symptoms (identical to depressive symptoms) are triggered by IL-1β, IL-6, and TNF-α acting directly on brain circuits including the prefrontal cortex, hippocampus, and reward pathways."
