              "explanation": "The PATHOS-D model proposes that modern MDD represents the misfiring of an evolutionarily adaptive 'Pathogen Host Defense' system. In ancestral environments, behaviors now recognized as depression (social withdrawal, reduced activity, appetite change) were protective during infection/injury. In modern settings without pathogenic threat, this circuit is triggered by psychosocial stressors, producing maladaptive depression."
