              "id": "case-lam",
              "title": "The Rash That Can Kill",
              "type": "case",
              "content": "**Three weeks** after starting lamotrigine, your nurse calls: \"Your patient Michael, 27M, is on the phone. He says he has a new rash on his trunk and mouth. He's been titrating slowly like you said.\"\n\nMichael is 27M, started at 25mg/week, now at 75mg. He is otherwise well.\n\n**As you read:** How do you risk-stratify this rash? What features distinguish benign drug rash from SJS/TEN? What is your immediate action?"
