              "explanation": "Ramelteon (melatonin receptor agonist) is the safest option in elderly patients — it is not on the Beers Criteria and has no dependence potential, no CNS depression, and no anticholinergic effects. Zolpidem and lorazepam are explicitly on the Beers Criteria for elderly due to fall and fracture risk. Diphenhydramine is also on Beers Criteria (anticholinergic effects — cognitive impairment, urinary retention)."
