              "explanation": "Trazodone's key advantage for chronic insomnia is the absence of physical dependence and withdrawal syndrome — unlike benzodiazepines and Z-drugs which can cause tolerance, dependence, and rebound insomnia on discontinuation. Trazodone's sedating properties come from 5-HT2A and H1 receptor antagonism. Key cautions: orthostatic hypotension and rare priapism (painful sustained erection — medical emergency)."
