              "explanation": "CBT-I (Cognitive Behavioral Therapy for Insomnia) is universally recommended as first-line treatment for chronic insomnia by major sleep societies (AASM, American College of Physicians). CBT-I includes stimulus control, sleep restriction therapy, sleep hygiene, and cognitive restructuring. Multiple meta-analyses show superior long-term outcomes compared to pharmacotherapy. Medications are appropriate as adjuncts or when CBT-I is unavailable/ineffective."
