              "type": "text",
              "title": "Buprenorphine Induction: Step by Step",
              "content": "## Step 1: Confirm Objective Withdrawal\n\nCOWS score ≥ 8–12 before first dose. The patient should have objective signs: elevated pulse, sweating, gooseflesh, GI symptoms, restlessness. Patient-reported discomfort alone is insufficient.\n\n## Step 2: First Dose\n\nStart with 2–4mg sublingual buprenorphine/naloxone. Hold under tongue for 5–10 minutes. Reassess in 45–60 minutes. If COWS improving and no precipitated withdrawal, give additional 2–4mg. Day 1 total dose is usually 8–16mg.\n\n## Step 3: Titration\n\nTypical maintenance dose 16–24mg/day. Doses up to 32mg are approved. Do not underdose — inadequate dosing leads to continued use and dropout.\n\n## Step 4: Ongoing Care\n\nUrine drug screens, PDMP checks, behavioral counseling, and regular follow-up. MAT is not a standalone treatment — the medication enables engagement in psychosocial treatment.",
