              "explanation": "The Bush-Francis Catatonia Rating Scale screens for and grades catatonic signs: immobility/stupor, mutism, staring, posturing/catalepsy, waxy flexibility, withdrawal, refusal to eat/drink, echophenomena (echolalia/echopraxia), negativism, and others. It guides diagnosis and treatment response monitoring."
