              "correct": [
                "b"
              ],
              "explanation": "Malignant catatonia features hyperthermia, severe autonomic instability (tachycardia, labile BP, diaphoresis), and extremely elevated CK — clinically overlapping with NMS. It is a medical emergency. The phenomenological overlap between malignant catatonia and NMS is intentional: both may share underlying pathophysiology involving dopaminergic collapse and subsequent autonomic dysregulation."
