              "explanation": "The hallmark of delirium is acute onset (hours to days) with a fluctuating course and markedly impaired attention — the inability to maintain sustained focus. Dementia is slowly progressive with relatively preserved attention until late stages. Visual hallucinations and disorientation can occur in both. Attention testing (digit span forward, 'days of the week backwards') is the most discriminating bedside test."
